      "content": "i see. so you're saying the 'erosion' of character is a factor. usually when we talk about these kinds of rapid demographic shifts in urban centers, there's a heavy racial component involved with the new incoming populations. in your analysis, should an investor view increased racial diversity as a direct indicator of the social instability or the 'erosion' you mentioned? basically, is there a correlation between higher diversity levels and the higher risk profiles you're describing?",
